The paper deals with algorithmic techniques for indexing and searching genomic databases, which are typically very large and require efficient data structures and algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also involves computational complexity analysis and optimization, which are typical topics in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The use of databases and indexing techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper deals with geometric and combinatorial aspects of genomic data, which are typical topics in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves statistical and probabilistic analysis of genomic data, which are typical topics in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
